8.  OUTPUT PRODUCTS AND AVAILABILITY                                            
                                                                                
8.1  Tape Products.                                                             
                                                                                
8.1.1  SAGE I Profile Archival Tape, Level II                     
                                                                                
       Medium/Specification:  9-track, 6250-bpi computer tape.                  
                                                                                
       Format and Content:  The tape is generated on a Control Data Corp.
       (CDC) Cyber-series computer.  Each record contains one event and is    
       688 60-bit fields in length.  Each field is in CDC-Cyber floating
       point notation.  Each record contains the event time and location, 
       the type of event (sunrise [0] or sunset [1]), meteorological data,  
       processing information, ground distances, quality factors for the 
       .600 micrometer wavelength measurements, and arrays of number 
       density and mixing ratio.

       Data Quantity/Rate:  Each magnetic tape contains one year of ozone 
       profiles beginning with December and ending with November of the 
       next year.  For year one of SAGE I (1979), the tape begins in late 
       February (first data of instrument).
                                                                                
       Status:  Available
                                                                                
       Plans/Schedule:  No additions or changes are expected.               
                                                                                
8.1.2  SAGE II Profile Archival Tape, Level II                   
                                                                                
       Medium/Specification:  9-track, 6250-bpi computer tape.               
   
       Format and Content:  The SAGE II ozone profile tapes are the same 
       format as the SAGE I tapes.  Each record represents one profile and
       is 680 60-bit Cyber floating-point words long (39 660 total bits per 
       record).  An end-of-tape mark signals the end of the data.  This tape
       contains processed ozone concentration profiles along with associated 
       error estimates.          
          
       Data Quantity/Rate:   Each magnetic tape contains one year of ozone 
       profiles beginning with December and ending with November of the 
       next year.  For year one of SAGE II (1985), the tapes also include 
       the November 1984 profile.
                                
       Status:  Available.                               
                                                                                
       Plans/Schedule:  NCDS plans to archive all SAGE I and SAGE II
       profile tapes.                                 
                                                                                
8.2  Film Products.   None.                            
                                                                                
